simphony.settings

Class SettingsRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Dictionary<K,V>
      • java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
        • simphony.settings.SettingsRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>

    public class SettingsRegistry
extends java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
    This is a simple class for storing settings for an application. This is at heart just a chain of Maps with an id assosciated to them. This stores that id in itself through the key REGISTRY_ID_KEY.
    Author:
    Jerry Vos

        public java.lang.Object get(java.lang.Object key)
        This will try to find a value for the specified key in this registry, and if it cannot it will attempt to find one in the next registry (which also will attempt to check in itself and then the next, ...).

      • put

        public java.lang.Object put(java.lang.String key,
                   java.lang.Object value)
        This attempts to find a registry with the given key already stored in it. If it cannot find one it will add the key and value to itself. If it can find one with the specified key it will set that value on that registry.
        Specified by:
        put in interface java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>

      • getRegistry

        public static SettingsRegistry getRegistry(java.lang.String registryId,
                           java.lang.String fileName)
        Retrives a static registry with the specified key. If another settings registry has been created with the specified id (using this method) that registry will be returned. If no registry has been created with the specified id, this will attempt to read one in using the specified file name. If reading the file name fails then a new SettingsRegistry will be created and returned.
        Parameters:
        registryId - the id of the registry
        fileName - the name of the settings file+
        Returns:
        a SettingsRegistry
        See Also:
        SettingsIO.loadSettings(String, String)

      • getRegistry

        public static SettingsRegistry getRegistry(java.lang.String registryId)
        Retrives a static registry with the specified key. If no registry has been created or registered with the specified id, this will return null.
        Parameters:
        registryId - the id of the registry
        Returns:
        a SettingsRegistry
        See Also:
        getRegistry(String), register(SettingsRegistry)

      • register

        public static SettingsRegistry register(SettingsRegistry registry)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
